        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 2:14PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 214 PM EDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm over Covington, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail, frequent cloud to ground
lightning and increased chance of a brief tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...While winds should result in minor damage to tree limbs and
blowing around of light, unsecured objects, this storm has
also exhibited localized rotation. A brief tornado could
quickly form.

Locations impacted include...
Covington, Madison, Oxford, Porterdale, Rutledge, Newborn, Mansfield,
Farrar, Starrsville, and Brick Store.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
central and north central Georgia.</instruction>
